newsitem.title: USA: PSE says to delist Latex, Thermwood debt.
newsitem.headline: PSE says to delist Latex, Thermwood debt.

text.p: The Pacific Stock Exchange (PSE) said on Wednesday it planned to delist the common stock and warrants of Latex Resources Inc.
It also said it would delist the 12-1/2 percent convertible subordinated debentures due February 25, 2003, of Thermwood Corp.
The exchange said Latex Resources has failed to comply with its minimum share bid price. The stock last traded on April 16 and closed at 1/2.
The PSE said Thermwood has failed to comply with its minimum requirements for principal amount outstanding and beneficial holders.
It said the delistings are subject to approval by the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.
